defs.docs: **A fast bump allocation arena for Rust.**

defs.name: collections
defs.docs: Collection types.

defs.name: vec
defs.docs:
A contiguous growable array type with heap-allocated contents, written
 `Vec<'bump, T>`.

defs.name: Vec
defs.docs: A contiguous growable array type, written `Vec<'bump, T>` but pronounced 'vector'.

defs.name: new_in
defs.docs: Constructs a new, empty `Vec<'bump, T>`.

defs.name: with_capacity_in
defs.value: fn (capacity: usize, bump: &'bump Bump) -> Vec<'bump, T>
defs.docs: Constructs a new, empty `Vec<'bump, T>` with the specified capacity.

defs.name: from_iter_in
defs.value: fn <I> (iter: I, bump: &'bump Bump) -> Vec<'bump, T>
defs.docs: Construct a new `Vec` from the given iterator's items.

defs.name: from_raw_parts_in
defs.value: fn (ptr: *mut T, length: usize, capacity: usize, bump: &'bump Bump) -> Vec<'bump, T>
defs.docs: Creates a `Vec<'bump, T>` directly from the raw components of another vector.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs:
Returns the number of elements the vector can hold without
 reallocating.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Reserves capacity for at least `additional` more elements to be inserted
 in the given `Vec<'bump, T>`. The collection may reserve more space to avoid
 frequent reallocations. After calling `reserve`, capacity will be
 greater than or equal to `self.len() + additional`. Does nothing if
 capacity is already sufficient.

defs.name: reserve_exact
defs.docs:
Reserves the minimum capacity for exactly `additional` more elements to
 be inserted in the given `Vec<'bump, T>`. After calling `reserve_exact`,
 capacity will be greater than or equal to `self.len() + additional`.
 Does nothing if the capacity is already sufficient.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs: Shrinks the capacity of the vector as much as possible.

defs.name: into_bump_slice
defs.docs: Converts the vector into `&'bump [T]`.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs:
Shortens the vector, keeping the first `len` elements and dropping
 the rest.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: Extracts a slice containing the entire vector.

defs.name: as_mut_slice
defs.docs: Extracts a mutable slice of the entire vector.

defs.name: set_len
defs.docs: Sets the length of a vector.

defs.name: swap_remove
defs.docs: Removes an element from the vector and returns it.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, index: usize, element: T) -> ()
defs.docs:
Inserts an element at position `index` within the vector, shifting all
 elements after it to the right.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs:
Removes and returns the element at position `index` within the vector,
 shifting all elements after it to the left.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the elements specified by the predicate.

defs.name: dedup_by_key
defs.value: fn <F, K> (&mut self, mut key: F) -> ()
defs.docs:
Removes all but the first of consecutive elements in the vector that resolve to the same
 key.

defs.name: dedup_by
defs.docs:
Removes all but the first of consecutive elements in the vector satisfying a given equality
 relation.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Appends an element to the back of a collection.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs:
Removes the last element from a vector and returns it, or [`None`] if it
 is empty.

defs.name: append
defs.docs: Moves all the elements of `other` into `Self`, leaving `other` empty.

defs.name: drain
defs.docs:
Creates a draining iterator that removes the specified range in the vector
 and yields the removed items.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Clears the vector, removing all values.

defs.name: len
defs.docs:
Returns the number of elements in the vector, also referred to
 as its 'length'.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the vector contains no elements.

defs.name: split_off
defs.docs: Splits the collection into two at the given index.

defs.name: resize
defs.value: fn (&mut self, new_len: usize, value: T) -> ()
defs.docs: Resizes the `Vec` in-place so that `len` is equal to `new_len`.

defs.name: extend_from_slice
defs.docs: Clones and appends all elements in a slice to the `Vec`.

defs.name: dedup
defs.docs:
Removes consecutive repeated elements in the vector according to the
 [`PartialEq`] trait implementation.

defs.name: splice
defs.value: fn <R, I> (&mut self, range: R, replace_with: I) -> Splice<I::IntoIter>
defs.docs:
Creates a splicing iterator that replaces the specified range in the vector
 with the given `replace_with` iterator and yields the removed items.
 `replace_with` does not need to be the same length as `range`.

defs.name: IntoIter
defs.docs: An iterator that moves out of a vector.

defs.name: as_slice
defs.docs: Returns the remaining items of this iterator as a slice.

defs.name: as_mut_slice
defs.docs: Returns the remaining items of this iterator as a mutable slice.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator for `Vec<'bump, T>`.

defs.name: Splice
defs.docs: A splicing iterator for `Vec`.

defs.name: DrainFilter
defs.docs: An iterator produced by calling `drain_filter` on Vec.

defs.name: string
defs.docs: A UTF-8 encoded, growable string.

defs.name: String
defs.docs: A UTF-8 encoded, growable string.

defs.name: FromUtf8Error
defs.docs: A possible error value when converting a `String` from a UTF-8 byte vector.

defs.name: FromUtf16Error
defs.docs: A possible error value when converting a `String` from a UTF-16 byte slice.

defs.name: new_in
defs.docs: Creates a new empty `String`.

defs.name: with_capacity_in
defs.docs: Creates a new empty `String` with a particular capacity.

defs.name: from_utf8
defs.docs: Converts a vector of bytes to a `String`.

defs.name: from_utf8_lossy_in
defs.docs: Converts a slice of bytes to a string, including invalid characters.

defs.name: from_utf16_in
defs.docs:
Decode a UTF-16 encoded vector `v` into a `String`, returning [`Err`]
 if `v` contains any invalid data.

defs.name: from_str_in
defs.docs: Construct a new `String<'bump>` from an iterator of `char`s.

defs.name: from_iter_in
defs.docs: Construct a new `String<'bump>` from an iterator of `char`s.

defs.name: from_raw_parts_in
defs.value: fn (buf: *mut u8, length: usize, capacity: usize, bump: &'bump Bump) -> String<'bump>
defs.docs: Creates a new `String` from a length, capacity, and pointer.

defs.name: from_utf8_unchecked
defs.docs:
Converts a vector of bytes to a `String` without checking that the
 string contains valid UTF-8.

defs.name: into_bytes
defs.docs: Converts a `String` into a byte vector.

defs.name: into_bump_str
defs.docs:
Convert this `String<'bump>` into a `&'bump str`. This is analagous to
 `std::string::String::into_boxed_str`.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Extracts a string slice containing the entire `String`.

defs.name: as_mut_str
defs.docs: Converts a `String` into a mutable string slice.

defs.name: push_str
defs.docs: Appends a given string slice onto the end of this `String`.

defs.name: capacity
defs.docs: Returns this `String`'s capacity, in bytes.

defs.name: reserve
defs.docs:
Ensures that this `String`'s capacity is at least `additional` bytes
 larger than its length.

defs.name: reserve_exact
defs.docs:
Ensures that this `String`'s capacity is `additional` bytes
 larger than its length.

defs.name: shrink_to_fit
defs.docs: Shrinks the capacity of this `String` to match its length.

defs.name: push
defs.docs: Appends the given [`char`] to the end of this `String`.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Returns a byte slice of this `String`'s contents.

defs.name: truncate
defs.docs: Shortens this `String` to the specified length.

defs.name: pop
defs.docs: Removes the last character from the string buffer and returns it.

defs.name: remove
defs.docs: Removes a [`char`] from this `String` at a byte position and returns it.

defs.name: retain
defs.docs: Retains only the characters specified by the predicate.

defs.name: insert
defs.value: fn (&mut self, idx: usize, ch: char) -> ()
defs.docs: Inserts a character into this `String` at a byte position.

defs.name: insert_str
defs.docs: Inserts a string slice into this `String` at a byte position.

defs.name: as_mut_vec
defs.docs: Returns a mutable reference to the contents of this `String`.

defs.name: len
defs.docs: Returns the length of this `String`, in bytes.

defs.name: is_empty
defs.docs: Returns `true` if this `String` has a length of zero.

defs.name: split_off
defs.docs: Splits the string into two at the given index.

defs.name: clear
defs.docs: Truncates this `String`, removing all contents.

defs.name: drain
defs.value: fn <'a, R> (&'a mut self, range: R) -> Drain<'a, 'bump>
defs.docs:
Creates a draining iterator that removes the specified range in the `String`
 and yields the removed `chars`.

defs.name: replace_range
defs.docs:
Removes the specified range in the string,
 and replaces it with the given string.
 The given string doesn't need to be the same length as the range.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Returns a slice of [`u8`]s bytes that were attempted to convert to a `String`.

defs.name: into_bytes
defs.docs: Returns the bytes that were attempted to convert to a `String`.

defs.name: utf8_error
defs.docs: Fetch a `Utf8Error` to get more details about the conversion failure.

defs.name: Drain
defs.docs: A draining iterator for `String`.

defs.name: CapacityOverflow
defs.docs:
Error due to the computed capacity exceeding the collection's maximum
 (usually `isize::MAX` bytes).

defs.name: AllocErr
defs.docs: Error due to the allocator (see the `AllocErr` type's docs).

defs.name: CollectionAllocErr
defs.docs: Augments `AllocErr` with a CapacityOverflow variant.

defs.name: AllocErr
defs.docs:
The `AllocErr` error indicates an allocation failure
 that may be due to resource exhaustion or to
 something wrong when combining the given input arguments with this
 allocator.

defs.name: Bump
defs.docs: An arena to bump allocate into.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Construct a new arena to bump allocate into.

defs.name: reset
defs.docs: Reset this bump allocator.

defs.name: alloc
defs.docs:
Allocate an object in this `Bump` and return an exclusive reference to
 it.

defs.name: alloc_with
defs.docs:
Pre-allocate space for an object in this `Bump`, initializes it using
 the closure, then returns an exclusive reference to it.

defs.name: alloc_slice_copy
defs.docs:
`Copy` a slice into this `Bump` and return an exclusive reference to
 the copy.

defs.name: alloc_slice_clone
defs.docs:
`Clone` a slice into this `Bump` and return an exclusive reference to
 the clone. Prefer `alloc_slice_copy` if `T` is `Copy`.

defs.name: alloc_layout
defs.docs: Allocate space for an object with the given `Layout`.

defs.name: each_allocated_chunk
defs.docs:
Call `f` on each chunk of allocated memory that this arena has bump
 allocated into.
